  "prompt": "What will be effect on stock exchange of India after ban on 500 and 1000 note?",
  "response": "When the Indian government demonetized \u20b9500 and \u20b91000 notes on November 8, 2016, it had significant effects on the stock market:\n\nShort-term effects:\n1. Initial market volatility and sharp decline\n2. Sensex and Nifty experienced significant drop\n3. Banking and financial stocks were most impacted\n4. Reduced liquidity in the market\n\nMedium-term effects:\n1. Increased digital transactions\n2. Shift towards formal banking\n3. Reduced cash-based transactions\n4. Temporary economic slowdown\n\nPositive long-term impacts:\n1. Improved transparency in financial markets\n2. Reduced black money circulation\n3. Enhanced digital payment infrastructure\n4. Increased tax compliance\n5. Lower interest rates due to increased bank deposits\n\nSector-specific impacts:\n1. Banking stocks initially fell but later recovered\n2. Real estate and jewelry sectors experienced significant disruption\n3. Digital payment companies saw substantial growth\n4. Cash-intensive businesses faced challenges\n\nOverall, while the short-term market reaction was negative, the long-term structural changes were considered beneficial for the Indian economy and stock market.\n\nNote: These effects were based on the actual implementation and subsequent market responses during and after demonetization.",
